Adam Scott leads  Phil Mickelson  and
 Lee Westwood  by one shot in the final round of the British Open.  Scott is 2 under par at Muirfield in Gullane, Scotland. The
Australian moved into the lead with four birdies over a five-hole stretch between the seventh and 11th holes.  Mickelson made consecutive birdies on the 13th and 14th
holes to reach 1 under. Westwood, who brought a two-shot lead
into todayâ€™s play, is 2 over through 10 holes.  Tiger Woods is 4 over for this round and trails Scott by
